    <!-- Code -->
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-pretty">Code</h2>
      <CodeBlock code={menubarCode} lang="html" />
    </div>

    <!-- Usage -->
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-pretty">Usage</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold">Structure</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">A menubar is composed of a horizontal container with multiple dropdown menus. Each menu button triggers a popover containing menu items, separators, and optional keyboard shortcut hints.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold">CSS Classes</h3>
          <div class="mt-2 space-y-2 text-sm">
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-1">
              <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
                <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">.mw-popover</code>
                <span class="text-muted-foreground">Container for the dropdown menu content</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
                <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">.mw-menu-item</code>
                <span class="text-muted-foreground">Individual menu item with hover and focus states</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
                <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">.mw-menu-separator</code>
                <span class="text-muted-foreground">Visual divider between menu item groups</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
                <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">.mw-menu-label</code>
                <span class="text-muted-foreground">Optional label for menu sections</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
                <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">.mw-kbd</code>
                <span class="text-muted-foreground">Keyboard shortcut indicator</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
                <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">.mw-btn-ghost</code>
                <span class="text-muted-foreground">Subtle button style for menu triggers</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
                <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">.mw-btn-sm</code>
                <span class="text-muted-foreground">Smaller button size for compact menus</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold">Alpine.js API</h3>
          <div class="mt-2 space-y-2 text-sm">
            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Each menu uses <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">x-data="mwDropdown()"</code> for state management.</p>
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-1">
              <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
                <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">toggle()</code>
                <span class="text-muted-foreground">Toggles the dropdown open/closed state</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
                <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">close()</code>
                <span class="text-muted-foreground">Closes the dropdown (used with @click.outside)</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
                <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">open</code>
                <span class="text-muted-foreground">Boolean property tracking dropdown state</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold">Layout Tips</h3>
          <div class="mt-2 space-y-2">
            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Use <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">border-b border-border</code> to create a horizontal divider below the menubar, mimicking native desktop application menus.</p>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Add <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">justify-between</code> to menu items to align keyboard shortcuts to the right.</p>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Combine <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">.mw-kbd</code> elements with text separators for multi-key shortcuts (e.g., Ctrl+Shift+S).</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold">Accessibility</h3>
          <div class="mt-2 space-y-2">
            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Menu buttons should have descriptive labels (File, Edit, View, Help) for screen readers.</p>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Use <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">x-cloak</code> to prevent flash of unstyled content during Alpine.js initialization.</p>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">The <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">@click.outside</code> directive ensures menus close when clicking elsewhere, matching expected behavior.</p>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Consider adding <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">@keydown.escape</code> handlers to close menus with the Escape key for keyboard navigation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
